Quick Plots for Toxics Report

Ben Best

January 10, 2018

1420.2 Sample History

Timeseries of Pb per Facility over Years

library(tidyverse)
library(readxl)
library(here)
library(DT)

d_xlsx <- here("data/1420.2 Sample History.xlsx")

d <- read_excel(d_xlsx) %>%
  mutate(
    yr_beg = `AR YEARS` %>%
      str_replace("(.*)-(.*)", "\\1") %>%
      as.integer())

d2 = d %>%
  select(facility=FACILITY, yr_beg, pb_hi=`Pb (high)`, pb_lo=`Pb (low)`) %>%
  filter(!is.na(pb_hi) & !is.na(pb_lo)) %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(
    pb_md = mean(c(pb_hi, pb_lo))) #View(d2)

p_pb_facilities <- ggplot(data=d2, aes(
  x = yr_beg, 
  y = pb_md, ymin = pb_lo, ymax = pb_hi,
  color =facility)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0.2) + geom_point() + geom_line()

p_pb_limits <- function(p){
  p +   
    # add hlines alphabetically
    # geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.0816, linetype="Benchmark"), color = "blue") +
    # geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.0025, linetype="CTR"), color = "green") +
    # geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.262 , linetype="NAL"), color = "red") +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.0816, linetype="Benchmark")) +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.0025, linetype="CTR")) +
    geom_hline(aes(yintercept=0.262 , linetype="NAL")) +
    scale_linetype_manual(
      name = "Limits", values = c(2, 3, 4)) #, 
      #guide = guide_legend(override.aes = list(color = c("blue", "green", "red"))))
}

p_pb_labs <- function(p, sub="Lead (log10 transformed) by year per facility"){
  p +   labs(subtitle=sub, 
       y="Pb (mg/L)", 
       x="Year", 
       title="Lead", 
       caption = "Source: 1420.2 Reports")
}

p_pb_facilities %>% 
  p_pb_limits() %>%
  p_pb_labs("Lead (log10 transformed) by year per facility")

Figure #. Timeseries of lead values per facility over years. Median values (point) are derived from the average of the high and low values (error bars) extracted from the 1420.2 reports. Limits (dashed lines) are shown for EPA Benchmark, NAL and CTR.

Timeseries of Pb per Facility over Years, log10

p_pb_facilities %>% 
  p_pb_limits() %>%
  p_pb_labs("Lead by year per facility") + 
  scale_y_log10(breaks=10^(-2:2))

Figure #. Timeseries of lead values per facility over years. Median values (point) are derived from the average of the high and low values (error bars) extracted from the 1420.2 reports. Note the log10 transformation of the y axis applied to show facility exceedance around the limits (dashed lines) for EPA Benchmark, NAL and CTR.

Boxplot of Pb across Facilities over Years

d3 <- d2 %>%
  gather(key, val, -facility, -yr_beg)

p_pb_box <- ggplot(data=d3, aes(x=as.factor(yr_beg), y=val)) +
  geom_boxplot() 

p_pb_box %>% 
  p_pb_limits() %>%
  p_pb_labs("Lead (log10 transformed) by year across facilities")

Figure #. Boxplot of lead values across facilities over years. Values for the boxplot are generated by including the high, low and average of the high and low values extracted from the 1420.2 reports. Limits (dashed lines) are shown for EPA Benchmark, NAL and CTR.

Boxplot of Pb across Facilities over Years, log10

p_pb_box %>% 
  p_pb_limits() %>%
  p_pb_labs("Lead (log10 transformed) by year across facilities") + 
  scale_y_log10(breaks=10^(-2:2))

Figure #. Boxplot of lead values across facilities over years. Values for the boxplot are generated by including the high, low and average of the high and low values extracted from the 1420.2 reports. Note the log10 transformation of the y axis applied to show facility exceedance around the limits (dashed lines) for EPA Benchmark, NAL and CTR.

Trojan 1994 to Present

Bar Plot

d_xlsx <- here("data/Trojan 1994 to Present.xlsx")
d <- read_excel(d_xlsx, na="no data")

d_na <- d %>% 
  filter(is.na(`Pb Concentration (mg/L)`)) %>%
  mutate(
    lbl = "NA",
    y   = 0)

g <- ggplot(d, aes(x=Year, y=`Pb Concentration (mg/L)`))
g + geom_col() +
  geom_text(
    aes(x=Year, y=y, label=lbl), data=d_na,
    size=3, vjust=-0.5)

Point Plot

g + geom_point()

Point & Line Plot

g + geom_point() + geom_line()
